  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TAF: ABC Fund Technical Assistance Facility Comp 3</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Each (potential) investee will be visited by the TAF  in collaboration with the fund managers  for a TA assessment including a ESG assessment and impact analysis. Based on the TA assessment and discussions with the fund manager and the investee  specific TA services will be designed and organised by the TAF under this project.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFAD and the EU have joined forces to set up the Agri-Business Capital Fund. The ABC Fundrsquo,s capital structure includes three tranches (A  B and C)  each offering a different risk return profile aimed at attracting various investor classes. An initial capital endowment of US$60 million in grant funding will be contributed by various donors (European Commission (EC)  Luxembourg  and AGRA) as first-loss equity (C-class)  which is expected to leverage around three times the amount in additional funding (A and B class)  or about US$180 million. The Fund design includes a TAF aimed at building the capacity of rural SMEs  Farmer Organizations (FOs) and Financial Intermediaries.The ABC fund is managed by Bamboo Capital and currently has USD 60 million in committed capital. The fund is meant to serve cooperatives and rural SMEs in mainly Sub-Saharan Africa (later to expand globally) by providing direct investments and smaller investments through local banks. The TAF grant is earmarked to provide technical assistance to cooperatives  rural SMEs and banks that will receive financing from the Agri-Business Capital fund.In this project all Technical Assistance services will be presented as advisory services  to be executed by representatives of Advance Consulting (SMEs)  Agriterra (FOs) and Rabo Partnerships (FIs). Managing a grant is a lot of work  and only part of the total grant will be for cooperative development services. But this grant has a lot of potential for us. While the initial grant is only for the first 3 years  the grant is renewable as fund is envisaged to have a fund life of 15 years. In addition  the fund is planned to grow to $ 260M  with the ideal TAF size at 15%-20% of total fund size.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of this project is to efficiently implement the TAF activities in collaboration with the ABC Fund managers and the TAF consortia members.</narrative>
  </description>
